    <body>
        <p>Converts the cursor to Cursor mode, which lets you add a cursor bitmap to the image by clicking in the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">frame</MadCap:conditionalText> and dragging in any direction. When you release the cursor, a cursor is added within a shaded oval shape. You can change the cursor type and adjust the color and transparency of the oval background from the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">Object</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">Cursor</MadCap:conditionalText> Properties <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">dialog</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">window pane</MadCap:conditionalText>.  <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Interface/UI_Elements/Cursor_Properties_Dialog.htm" target="" title="" alt="" MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">Cursor Properties Dialog</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Interface/UI_Elements/Object_Properties_Window_Pane.htm#CursorObjectProperties" MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">Cursor Properties</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
    </body>
</html>